  "text": "Whether the absence of an initial peak is the result of an impaired neurogenic response in our patient group remains to be elucidated. The vasodilation induced by exogenous ACh in human skin is mainly mediated by the release of NO from the endothelium through activation 275 of NOS, although part of the response is mediated by prostaglandins, and possibly other factors [CITATION_1] .",
